Create a AssociatedKeyImpl object.

Parameters:
name - the name of the key property in the DTO
keyType - the type of key in the foreign DTO (Sequence, Composite, etc.)
parentName - the name of the parent DTO type for a composite key
prefix - the prefix for the key in the DTO
typeName - the data type of the key in the foreign DTO
packageName - the data-access layer package of the data type
tableName - the SQL table name of the foreign DTO
required - whether the key is required in the current DTO
objectName - the name of the key object in the Java class (type name or property name if duplication present)
businessPackageName - the business-layer package of the data type
subsystemName - the name of the subsystem that contains the data type
generalization - whether the associated key represents the generalization/inheritance relationship to the superclass(es)
persistent - whether the associated key represents a database foreign key or a transient association only
readWrite - whether the associated object is read/write
keyProperties - the collection of key attributes
